You’re comparing LogisticRegression vs LinearSVC on the same dataset and want identical preprocessing (imputation + scaling + one-hot). You want to swap only the estimator without duplicating preprocessing code, and you want to grid-search estimator-specific hyperparameters. Which parameter grid structure is correct when the estimator is a pipeline step named 'clf'?

A) param_grid = {'C': [0.1, 1], 'clf': [LogisticRegression(), LinearSVC()]}
B) param_grid = [{'clf': [LogisticRegression()], 'clf__C': [0.1, 1]}, {'clf': [LinearSVC()], 'clf__C': [0.1, 1]}]
C) param_grid = {'clf__estimator': [LogisticRegression(), LinearSVC()], 'C': [0.1, 1]}
D) param_grid = {'model': [LogisticRegression(), LinearSVC()], 'model__C': [0.1, 1]}
